  <thing id="gGurch" name="Gurch (Poison)" description="Dark green liquid or powder, smells like wax.\n\nDC 17 spot check to notice.\n\nContact DC 17\n\nInitial Damage 1d8 Damage\n\nSecondary Damage 1D2 Strength damage every minute for 5 minutes. In addition if the victim fails his save against the secondary damage he is wracked with excruciating pain that renders him unable to move.\n\nThe victim becomes paralysed for as long as the poison continues to deal him damage.\n\nA successful save against the poison&apos;s secondary damage negates all later damage (and paralysis) as well. {i}Neutralise poison{/i} stops the damage and removes the paralysis caused by it.\n\nPerils Of Using Poison\n\nA character has a 5% chance of exposing himself to a poison whenever he applies it to a weapon or otherwise readies it for use. Additionally, a character who rolls a natural 1 on an attack roll with a poisoned weapon must make a DC 15 Reflex save or accidentally poison himself with the weapon. A creature with a poison attack is immune to its own poison and the poison of others of its kind.\n\n{b}Source{/b}: Dragon Compendium" compset="Gear" summary="Poison Vials contain 1 dose of poison only, the charges do not stack add individual vials singularly! Gurch (Poison)" stacking="merge">
