  <thing id="gVedya" name="Vedya (Poison)" description="Pale purple liquid or powder, smells like raisins.\n\nDC 18 Spot check to notice \n\nContact DC 22\n\nInitial Damage None\n\nSecondary Damage 1d4 Constitution damage.\n\nVedya is a persistent alchemically enhanced poison that deals stitution damage as its secondary damage. If its victim fails his save to resist the poison&apos;s secondary damage, the poison takes on the\nproperties of a disease and continues to deal 1d4 points of Constitution damage every day until he dies, makes four successful Fortitude saves in a row (one each day, as a disease), or receives magical healing. \n\nBecause of vedya&apos;s alchemical potency it is immune to any spell short of {i}lesser wish, miracle, or wish{/i}. The damage it deals, however, can be cured normally. \n\nPerils Of Using Poison\n\nA character has a 5% chance of exposing himself to a poison whenever he applies it to a weapon or otherwise readies it for use. Additionally, a character who rolls a natural 1 on an attack roll with a poisoned weapon must make a DC 15 Reflex save or accidentally poison himself with the weapon. A creature with a poison attack is immune to its own poison and the poison of others of its kind.\n\n{b}Source{/b}: Dragon Compendium" compset="Gear" summary="Poison Vials contain 1 dose of poison only, the charges do not stack add individual vials singularly! Vedya (Poison)" stacking="merge">
