  <thing id="gStirgeSw" name="Stirge Sweat (Poison)" description="Brownish, sap-like liquid. \n\nInjury DC 16\n\nInitial Damage None.\n\nSecondary Damage 1d4 points of Strength damage 1 minute later as usual and then another 1 point of Strength damage 1 minute after that. \n\nA successful save against the poison&apos;s secondary damage negates all later damage as well.\n\nINJURY POISONS\n\nInjury poisons usually come naturally from poisonous animals. Most often they find use coating a piercing or slashing weapon.\n\nPerils Of Using Poison\n\nA character has a 5% chance of exposing himself to a poison whenever he applies it to a weapon or otherwise readies it for use. Additionally, a character who rolls a natural 1 on an attack roll with a poisoned weapon must make a DC 15 Reflex save or accidentally poison himself with the weapon. A creature with a poison attack is immune to its own poison and the poison of others of its kind.\n\n{b}Source{/b}: Dragon Compendium" compset="Gear" summary="Poison Vials contain 1 dose of poison only, the charges do not stack add individual vials singularly! Stirge Sweat (Poison)" stacking="merge">
